<p>How can I read from the same stream twice or more?</p>  <p>I have a file with 3000 lines and this program tells me it only loops over the stream once:</p>  <pre><code>#include &lt;iostream&gt; #include &lt;fstream&gt;  void func(std::ifstream&amp; is) {     std::string dummy;     int i = 0;     while(std::getline(is, dummy))     {         ++i;     }     std::cout &lt;&lt; i &lt;&lt; std::endl; }  int main() {     std::ifstream is("testfile");     func(is);     func(is); } </code></pre>  <p>output:</p>  <pre><code>3000 0 </code></pre>